modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and generating OCaml code from IDL (Interface Definition Language) specifications. Operates on abstract syntax trees and source code strings to translate interface descriptions into executable OCaml modules. Used to automate the creation of client and server code for distributed systems.

Provides functions to manage COM interface interactions, including querying interfaces by IID, converting between interface types, and combining interface pointers. Works with COM-specific types such as `interface`, `iid`, `clsid`, and `component_factory`. Used to create COM instances, register component factories, and parse interface identifiers from strings.
